24:36.357 --> 24:37.278
That's right. Planetary scientists use 
telescopes. Some of them use space probes,

24:39.400 --> 24:44.365
however, which are not really telescopes. It's 
more like a remote geologist. You may have too much

24:48.649 --> 24:51.392
knowledge to answer, so let me ask you this. You're 
the big cheese at the PASP, and you ought to have

24:51.412 --> 24:58.059
your finger on the pulse of this. Do you think the 
public believes planetary astronomy is part of

24:58.079 --> 25:02.083
astronomy? Oh, yes. Oh, yes. There's no doubt 
about that. When people ask general questions

25:06.547 --> 25:18.088
about astronomy or what draws them into the 
interest of astronomy overall, one very

25:06.547 --> 25:18.088
important part is planetary. After all, that's 
