25:21.394 --> 25:28.386
Granted, they're going to ask questions about the 
Big Bang or search for extraterrestrial

25:21.394 --> 25:28.386
intelligence. Let's not forget that the search 
for extraterrestrial intelligence is related to

25:28.602 --> 25:33.607
planetary systems. And the more we know about our 
planetary systems, for example, at the ASP, the

25:34.248 --> 25:52.425
questions I get from the press or radio and 
television stations, they increase enormously

25:34.248 --> 25:52.425
during the time when we have a lunar eclipse, a 
solar eclipse, a close cometary approach, a

25:34.248 --> 25:52.425
meteor shower. I mean, these are things that the 
public can easily identify because they can

25:52.625 --> 25:57.310
easily see them. So from the public's 
perspective, planetary astronomy may be the only

25:57.695 --> 26:04.704
part of astronomy they ever come in contact with. 
You think, you know, we've had 30 years and now we

